]]></contentSummary><contentType>website</contentType><subject>job perspective</subject><webLink xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[http://studieadres.nl]]></webLink></contentLink><programDescription xml:lang="en"><![CDATA[Housed within the largest Faculty of Humanities in the Netherlands, this programme is able to offer students the opportunity to study religion in a broad context, as well as unique opportunities for specialisation and interdisciplinary studies. Their is a strong focus on interactions of religious texts, traditions and practices with various cultures from a literary, historical and/or social sciences perspective.
]]></programDescription><programDescription xml:lang="nl"><![CDATA[Als je bijvoorbeeld wilt analyseren hoe die tradities en gebruiken in wisselwerking met verschillende culturen functioneren. Daarbij kun je historische, literaire, sociaal- en menswetenschappelijke en cultuur-analytische invalshoeken kiezen.

